2052.subject: ESSP
2052.descrlong: Students work with practicing professionals in the community in a volunteer or paid internship that does not require specialized science, policy, or technical skills. Academic credit is awarded for documented learning that takes place during the internship and that meets individualized and core internship outcomes. (Offered fall and spring semesters.)
